/* Infrastructure */  this is a 2009 report by the inspection committee in 2009 which has since been overturned as what they were saying was wrong
Amity is on the list of Association of Commonwealth Universites and Association of Indian Universties showing its standig and recognition
This is absolutely false and was part of a blackmailing campaign which was stopped
The cited article does not mention anything that is referred to
Amity is recognised and accredited by the University Grants Commission and is thus listed on their website

UGC has never denied recognition to Amity.  There was some confusion about listing private universities in general which the court clarified and then all private universities including Amity were listed

As is clear from the legal case shown at www.amity.edu/Admission/govt_recognition.asp , a University does not need AICTE permission.  To say that Amity does not have permission is thus misleading and wrong.
